==English==

===Etymology===
: From the 1896 edition of the International Cloud Atlas which defined ten types of cloud. The ninth cloud was the [[cumulo-nimbus]] rising to a height of 10 km, which is the highest a cloud can be. 

===Noun===
'''[[cloud]] [[nine]]'''
#(''informal'') a state of [[happiness]], [[elation]] or [[bliss]]; often used in the phrase [[on cloud nine]]
